Fix expl_duck_duck_go.py by adding user agent

With the default user agent, Duck Duck Go will not return search
results, and instead raise an error (maybe some anti-bot code?).

Thanks to @dillonko for the tip!

Revert "Update expl_duck_duck_go.py"

This reverts commit c3d11f0efa22db2492f668ff3b3b46938669c092.

The original selector was correct.

Example use of MechanicalSoup using Qwant

Our DuckDuckGo example doesn't work anymore, probably due to an
anti-bot feature on DuckDuckGo. This introduces and promotes in
README.rst an example that actually works.

form.py: improve warning in Form initialization

The `PendingDeprecationWarning` exception is suppressed by default,
which makes it not very helpful as a way to warn users about likely
incorrect usage. Switch to `FutureWarning`, which is not suppressed
by default.

Also fix a missing string formatting argument.

Also removed a near-duplicate entry that was erroneously merged into

ChangeLog.rst: fix malformed hyperlink

This hyperlink was missing its closing `>`.
Use new url, page and form properties in documentation

Use new url, page and form properties in implementation

Now that the getters are deprecated, stop using them even internally.

Patch obtained using

  perl -pi -e 's/\.get_url\(\)/.url/g' mechanicalsoup/*.py
  perl -pi -e 's/\.get_current_form\(\)/.form/g' mechanicalsoup/*.py
  perl -pi -e 's/\.get_current_page\(\)/.page/g' mechanicalsoup/*.py

followed by a whitespace PEP8 manual fix.

update tests to use the new url, page and form properties

Patch obtained using

  perl -pi -e 's/\.get_url\(\)/.url/g' tests/*.py
  perl -pi -e 's/\.get_current_form\(\)/.form/g' tests/*.py
  perl -pi -e 's/\.get_current_page\(\)/.page/g' tests/*.py

and then reverting the hunks for test_properties and
test_get_selected_form_unselected, and manually applying this:

--- a/tests/test_stateful_browser.py
+++ b/tests/test_stateful_browser.py
@@ -643,7 +643,8 @@ def test_refresh_form_not_retained():

     assert browser.url == url
     assert browser.page == reload_page
-    assert browser.form is None
+    with pytest.raises(AttributeError, match="No form has been selected yet."):
+        browser.form

Update examples with new properties (form, url, page)

Unfortunately, the duckduckgo example doesn't work anymore, most
likely duckduckgo has an anti-bot filter now.
ChangeLog.rst: add StatefulBrowser getter changes

Provide a helpful error message when no form is selected

Since the currently selected form can now be accessed with
`StatefulBrowser.form`, it may not be obvious to users why this
returns `None` if they haven't called `StatefulBrowser.select_form`
yet.

Raising an exception in this case makes it unambiguous that
`form` in this context means "selected form", and that to use
this property they will need to first select a form.

stateful_browser.py: add page, url, and form properties

Closes #175.

The most convenient way to access the page, url, and form objects
is to use properties, which are mapped to the appropriate getter
functions using `property`.

* get_current_page -> page property

  The previous method name was simply too long for such a commonly
  used function. The "current" adjective added no extra specificity.

* get_current_form -> form property

  This is changed for clarity. What is the "current" form if there
  are multiple forms on the page? Instead, we make it clearer by
  describing it as the "selected" form.

* get_url -> url property

  This is just an elimination of the get_ prefix and use a property.

For backwards compatibility, the older method names remain as aliases.

form.py: minor cleanup in new_control

Use a for-loop over input-like elements instead of writing them
all out.

Decompose select elements with the same name (#298)

Fixes #297
